        "title": "5. `notify.py` — env-var-gated side effects, currently untested",
        "content": "\n**Gaps:** each notifier's \"no-op when env unset\" branch, `dispatch`'s per-notifier exception isolation (a Slack failure must not block SMS), SMS body truncation/ASCII-only guarantee (there's an explicit comment about avoiding UCS-2 segments — that's a real bug surface).\n\n```python\nfrom notify import notify_slack, notify_sms, dispatch, _sms_body\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef test_notify_slack_noop_without_webhook_url(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n    notify_slack([Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"T\", url=\"u\")], [])\n    # assert no HTTP call made (patch httpx.post and assert not called)\n\ndef test_sms_body_is_ascii_only():\n    j = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"T\")\n    body = _sms_body([j], [])\n    assert body.isascii()\n\ndef test_sms_body_truncates_and_shows_overflow_count():\n    jobs = [Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=str(i), title=f\"T{i}\") for i in range(12)]\n    body = _sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n    assert \"+4 more\" in body\n\ndef test_dispatch_continues_after_one_notifier_raises(monkeypatch, capsys):\n    def boom(new, changed): raise RuntimeError(\"slack down\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"notify.NOTIFIERS\", [boom, notify_console])\n    dispatch([], [])\n    assert \"notifier boom failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n```\n\n",
